30.1-28-04. (5-304) Findings - Order of appointment.
1. The court shall exercise the authority conferred in this chapter consistent with the maximum
self-reliance and independence of the incapacitated person and make appointive and other
orders only to the extent necessitated by the incapacitated person's actual mental and
adaptive limitations or other conditions warranting the procedure.
2. At a hearing held under this chapter, the court shall:

